{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Issue Small-scale Renewable Energy Certificates (SREC) like Australia & USA",
        "additional_details": "This could help accelerate the transition for Net Zero and reduce national grid dependency & the country\u2019s overall emissions.\r\n \r\nSRECs allow individuals and businesses to make conscious choices for clean energy & be an active participant in the transition to a more sustainable energy.\r\n \r\nThis could also support job creation from installation and maintenance, to support local economics.\r\n \r\nThe mix of renewables could help increase energy security, reduce energy grid dependency, reduce the carbon footprint. SRECs provide a financial incentive for individuals and businesses by providing them with a certificate for each unit of energy they generate.",
        "background": "We want the Government to create financial incentives for new, small-scale renewable energy generation.",
